President Obama held a meeting with his national security team to discuss developments in Afghanistan and Pakistan. The President received updates on political developments in Afghanistan, including efforts to enhance governance and accountability, and the upcoming parliamentary elections. General Petraeus provided an update on the security situation, highlighting the completion of the deployment of additional troops and their focus on challenging Taliban strongholds, training Afghan Security Forces, and supporting reintegration and local policing initiatives. Ambassador Patterson discussed the challenges posed by recent flooding in Pakistan and ongoing efforts to provide humanitarian support. The President also reviewed efforts to combat al Qaeda in the border region, including cooperation with Pakistan, Afghanistan, and NATO allies.